Day 2 — Repository Types: Local, Remote, Virtual
This is the most fundamental concept in Artifactory. Every repository is one of three types.

1. Local Repository
A local storage repository — you own the artifacts here. Your CI/CD pipeline publishes artifacts to local repositories.

You have full control
Artifacts are physically stored inside Artifactory
Versions are tracked with full audit history
Examples: libs-release-local, docker-prod-local, pypi-local

CI/CD Build → publishes → Local Repository

2. Remote Repository
A proxy and cache for an external registry. When you request an artifact, Artifactory:

Checks its local cache — if found, serves it immediately
If not cached, fetches it from the remote source (Maven Central, Docker Hub, npmjs, etc.)
Caches it locally for future requests
Benefits:

Speed — cached artifacts served locally
Reliability — builds don't break if Docker Hub is down
Control — you can block specific packages
Security — only scanned artifacts enter your network

Developer/Build → requests → Remote Repository → (if not cached) → External Registry
                                     ↓
                              Caches locally

Common remote repos: npmjs-remote (proxy to npmjs.org), maven-central-remote, dockerhub-remote

3. Virtual Repository
An aggregation layer that combines multiple local and remote repositories behind a single URL. Your build tool points to one URL — Artifactory routes requests to the appropriate underlying repository.

Resolution order matters: Artifactory searches repositories in the order you configure.

Build tool → Virtual Repository URL
                    ↓
        ┌───────────────────────┐
        │ libs-release-local    │ (check here first)
        │ libs-snapshot-local   │ (check here second)
        │ maven-central-remote  │ (check here third)
        └───────────────────────┘

Why Virtual Repositories?

One URL for builds — no need to configure multiple sources in build tools
Add/remove underlying repos without changing build configs
Different virtual repos for dev vs prod (different resolution order, different permissions)
Naming Convention (Best Practice)
{team}-{technology}-{local/remote/virtual}-{environment}

libs-maven-local-release
libs-maven-remote-central
libs-maven-virtual-dev
docker-images-local-prod
